This is the landing page for Schedule Maker App. To build this landing page we will use HTML, CSS and Java Script.

## Landing Page Goals
- Convert visitors into app users
- Clearly communicate core value proposition for students
- Showcase key features with visual examples
- Create a clean, organized aesthetic that reflects the app's purpose

## HTML Structure
- Use semantic HTML5 elements (header, nav, main, section, footer)
- Implement proper heading hierarchy (h1, h2, h3)
- Include schema.org markup for improved SEO
- Ensure all interactive elements have appropriate ARIA attributes
- Create logical tab order for keyboard navigation

## CSS Guidelines
- Implement a responsive design that works on all device sizes
- Use CSS Grid and Flexbox for layout
- Define a consistent color palette that evokes focus and organization
- Maintain a clean typography system with no more than 2-3 font families
- Use CSS variables for theme colors, spacing, and typography
- Include smooth transitions and subtle animations for interactive elements

## JavaScript Guidelines
- Minimize JavaScript for the landing page - keep it lightweight
- Use vanilla JavaScript where possible
- Implement lazy loading for images and videos
- Create smooth scroll behavior for navigation links
- Add minimal interactive elements that showcase app functionality

## Landing Page Sections
1. **Hero Section**
   - Compelling headline focusing on student organization
   - Brief subheading explaining core value proposition
   - Primary CTA button (e.g., "Start Organizing Today" or "Try Free Version")
   - Hero image showing app interface on multiple devices

2. **Features Showcase**
   - Visual grid of key features with icons and brief descriptions
   - Focus on: Calendar, To-do lists, Focus mode, Progress tracking
   - Use interactive elements to demonstrate how features work

3. **User Benefits Section**
   - Address pain points: forgetting tasks, losing focus, feeling overwhelmed
   - Show transformation: from stressed to organized student
   - Include relevant statistics on productivity improvements

4. **How It Works**
   - Simple step-by-step guide with illustrations
   - Demonstrate ease of getting started
   - Show integration into student workflow

5. **Testimonials**
   - Quotes from student users highlighting different use cases
   - Include diverse representation of student types
   - Focus on specific results and improvements

6. **Pricing Section**
   - Clear comparison of free vs. premium tiers
   - Highlight value of premium features
   - Include prominent CTA buttons for each tier

7. **FAQ Section**
   - Address common questions about functionality, data privacy, etc.
   - Use accordion or tabbed interface for clean organization
   - Include link to more comprehensive support resources

8. **Footer**
   - App download links
   - Social media links
   - Privacy policy and terms of service
   - Contact information

## Performance Guidelines
- Optimize all images for web (WebP format with fallbacks)
- Aim for a perfect Lighthouse performance score
- Implement critical CSS for above-the-fold content
- Minimize third-party scripts and dependencies
- Set appropriate cache headers for static assets

## SEO Considerations
- Create unique, descriptive title and meta description
- Implement proper canonical tags
- Use descriptive alt text for all images
- Include relevant keywords naturally in content
- Implement Open Graph and Twitter card meta tags for social sharing

## Analytics Implementation
- Set up event tracking for all CTA buttons
- Track scroll depth to measure content engagement
- Implement funnel visualization for sign-up process
- Set up A/B testing capability for headline variations

## Accessibility Requirements
- Maintain WCAG 2.1 AA compliance
- Ensure color contrast ratios meet accessibility standards
- Provide text alternatives for all non-text content
- Ensure all functionality is keyboard accessible
- Test with screen readers for proper navigation

## Additional Elements
- Add subtle micro-interactions to increase engagement
- Include a newsletter signup for product updates
- Implement a chatbot or help widget for immediate assistance
- Add social proof elements (download counts, user ratings)